com.homework.S1_Computus_Hard

Class Computus

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.homework.S1_Computus_Hard.Computus

  • public class Computus
extends java.lang.Object
    Version:
    1.0

    Computus is built to compute the day and month of Easter with a given year. The methods bellow allow calculation and the ability to format the given date the way you want it.

    Author:
    Alex Wong wong4a@gmail.com

      • getYear

        public int getYear()
        This method is to return the year value that is in this class. Default value is 1818. Unless year gets set.
        Returns:
        the year in an integer form

      • setYear

        public void setYear(int year)
        This method is used to set a year value that will be used to calculate the day when Easter will occur.
        Parameters:
        year - year to be used to calculate the date of Easter

      • calculateMonthValue

        public int calculateMonthValue()
        This method will calculate the month value that Easter is on. This will give the value of 1 though 12 respective to the months.
        Returns:
        the month in integer form ex. 3

      • calculateDayValue

        public int calculateDayValue()
        This method will calculate the day value. It will give the value of 1 though 31 respective of the days in the corresponding month Easter is on.
        Returns:
        the day in integer form ex. 24

      • getMonthName

        public java.lang.String getMonthName()
        This method will convert the number that corresponds to the correct month and return it as a String. This will only display two different months that Easter occurs on.
        Returns:
        the month in String form ex. March

      • occurrenceDateDisplay

        public void occurrenceDateDisplay()
        This method will count the number of times Easter occurs on each day within a cycle of 5,700,000 years starting from the inputted year. It will print out the data collected.
